{"id": "duc04-testb-22:4#12", "contents": "The arrest of a former Bosnian Serb leader has brought new hope that two of the most wanted men, Radovan Karadzic and Ratko Mladic, will be brought to justice. The aide, Mirza Jajric, expressed optimism that the recent arrest would be a stepping stone in the pursuit of these notorious figures. The international community has been eager to see Karadzic and Mladic face trial for their alleged war crimes."}
